{"title_page": "Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9\n| image       = Jo dee Roo (links) wint Bordeaux-Parijs Rechts de Fransman Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9 die 2e, Bestanddeelnr 913-9818.jpg\n| full_name   = Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9\n| nickname    = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1930|09|02}}\n| birth_place = [[Arradon]], [[France]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|2015|5|31|1930|9|2}}\n| death_place = \n| height      = \n| weight      = \n| currentteam = \n| discipline  = Road\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = \n| proyears1   = \n| proteam1    = \n| majorwins   = One stage Tour de France\n}}\n\n'''Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9''' (September 2, 1930 \u2013 May 31, 2015) was a [[France|French]] professional [[road bicycle racer]]. He was professional from 1950 to 1965. Highlights from his career include one day in the yellow jersey as leader of the [[general classification in the Tour de France|general classification]] in the [[1953 Tour de France]], a stage win in [[1954 Tour de France]] as well as a stage win in [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], [[Paris\u2013Nice]], [[Tour de Luxembourg]] and the [[Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9|Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9]] and coming second in the 1952 edition of the [[GP Ouest-France]] and the 1954 edition of [[Tour of Flanders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Cyclisme-sur-route/Actualites/Deces-de-francois-mahe/563165|title=Disparition - D\u00e9c\u00e8s de Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9|work=L'Equipe.fr|language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1953\n:[[1953 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::Wearing [[yellow jersey]] for one day\n::10th place overall classification\n;1954\n:[[1954 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::Winner stage 21A\n;1955\n:Malansec\n:[[1955 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::10th place overall classification\n;1958\n:Querrien\n;1959\n:Bain-de-Bretagne\n:[[1959 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::5th place overall classification\n;1960\n:Brest\n:Camors\n:Chauffailles\n:Ploudalmezeau\n;1961\n:[[1961 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]:\n::Winner stages 2 and 14\n;1962\n:Ma\u00ebl-Carhaix\n:Pl\u00e9vin\n;1963\n:GP de Cannes\n;1965\n:Grandchamps\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://memoire-du-cyclisme.net/palmares/mahe_francois.php Palmar\u00e8s of Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9]\n*{{Cycling Archives|2207}}\n*[http://histo.letour.fr/HISTO/TDF/riders/us/3295.html Official Tour de France results for Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mahe, Francois}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:French Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:French Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Morbihan]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1930s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9\n| image       = Jo dee Roo (links) wint Bordeaux-Parijs Rechts de Fransman Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9 die 2e, Bestanddeelnr 913-9818.jpg\n| full_name   = Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9\n| nickname    = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1930|09|02}}\n| birth_place = [[Arradon]], [[France]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|2015|5|31|1930|9|2}}\n| death_place = \n| height      = \n| weight      = \n| currentteam = \n| discipline  = Road\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = \n| proyears1   = \n| proteam1    = \n| majorwins   = One stage Tour de France\n}}\n\n'''Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9''' (September 2, 1930 \u2013 May 31, 2015) was a [[France|French]] professional [[road bicycle racer]]. He was professional from 1950 to 1965. Highlights from his career include one day in the yellow jersey as leader of the [[general classification in the Tour de France|general classification]] in the [[1953 Tour de France]], a stage win in [[1954 Tour de France]] as well as a stage win in [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], [[Paris\u2013Nice]], [[Tour de Luxembourg]] and the [[Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9|Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9]] and coming second in the 1952 edition of the [[GP Ouest-France]] and the 1954 edition of [[Tour of Flanders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Cyclisme-sur-route/Actualites/Deces-de-francois-mahe/563165|title=Disparition - D\u00e9c\u00e8s de Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9|work=L'Equipe.fr|language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1953\n:[[1953 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::Wearing [[yellow jersey]] for one day\n::10th place overall classification\n;1954\n:[[1954 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::Winner stage 21A\n;1955\n:Malansec\n:[[1955 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::10th place overall classification\n;1958\n:Querrien\n;1959\n:Bain-de-Bretagne\n:[[1959 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::5th place overall classification\n;1960\n:Brest\n:Camors\n:Chauffailles\n:Ploudalmezeau\n;1961\n:[[1961 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]:\n::Winner stages 2 and 14\n;1962\n:Ma\u00ebl-Carhaix\n:Pl\u00e9vin\n;1963\n:GP de Cannes\n;1965\n:Grandchamps\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://memoire-du-cyclisme.net/palmares/mahe_francois.php Palmar\u00e8s of Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9]\n*{{Cycling Archives|2207}}\n*[http://histo.letour.fr/HISTO/TDF/riders/us/3295.html Official Tour de France results for Fran\u00e7ois Mah\u00e9]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mahe, Francois}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:French Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:French Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Morbihan]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1930s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\